#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Avijjāvagga "
msgstr "6. Ignorance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 53. Avijjāpahānasutta → avijjā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Avijjāpahānasutta "
msgstr "53. Giving Up Ignorance "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.31, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.53:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:1.3"
msgid "“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how does one know and see so as to give up ignorance and give rise to knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuṃ kho, bhikkhu, aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, knowing and seeing the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.2"
msgid "Rūpe aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.3"
msgid "Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.4"
msgid "cakkhusamphassaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.5"
msgid "yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. "
msgstr "And also knowing and seeing the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.6"
msgid "Sotaṃ … "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing the ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.7"
msgid "ghānaṃ … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.8"
msgid "jivhaṃ … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.9"
msgid "kāyaṃ … "
msgstr "body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.10"
msgid "manaṃ aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.11"
msgid "Dhamme … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.12"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.13"
msgid "manosamphassaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.14"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. "
msgstr "And also knowing and seeing the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.15"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how to know and see so as to give up ignorance and give rise to knowledge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.16"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

